JOHANNESBURG - Police Minister Fikile Mbalula on Wednesday said cops should create a conducive environment for farmers to produce and ensure food security for all South Africans. He said a national imbizo would be held before the end of the year to iron out plans to operationalise the Rural Safety Strategy. The minister revealed this following a meeting with Transvaal Agricultural Union (TAU) on Wednesday. INFOGRAPHIC: Farm murder numbers conundrum His office said the meeting formed part of ongoing meetings the minister has been having with different stakeholders. A number of farmers took to the streets in October protesting against farm killings across the country. READ: Farming communities stage mass protests on #BlackMonday The TAU President Louis Mentjies said the country needed more police visibility.  eNCA